<concept id="concept_3413BBD173324104B42FB714974CABE7" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Addressing the APIs - REST</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>The resources of Web services you develop using the REST APIs of <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> are addressed by their URLs in the following format: </p>
            <p><codeph>https://&lt;host>:&lt;port>/&lt;resource></codeph></p>
            <p><codeph>&lt;host></codeph> and <codeph>&lt;port></codeph> point to the server where the Web service has been deployed. <codeph>&lt;resource></codeph> is the path and name of the resource. </p>
            <p>Example:</p>
            <p><codeph>https://myServer:8081/mynotification/v1/processes</codeph></p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
